race.comment: Another big field with plenty of pressure. Like the chances of MADAME CODY (13) who resumes from a good spell. Made debut in town and was well in the market but very green and safely held. Has won two trials by a space and back in this company should run a huge race fresh. LIFT'N'MEHIGHER (9) is fitter for two runs back and did go close last time. Looks ready to fire and expected to feature. PIERANT (6) is a former NSW galloper who started big odds but ran very well fresh over an unsuitable journey. Extra trip a plus here and no surprise to see a return to form. LOPE BY NIGHT (17) is going well, the latest fifth here over 1200m. Expected to give a sight over the extra ground.
